additional $1,700,000 - to expand the benefits to these patients to include 
post-mastectomy radiation and breast reconstruction; or to provide the Minimum 
Package to an additional 93 uninsured women.
CONCLUSIONS: California legislators must decide whether to offer comprehensive 
benefits to a limited number of breast cancer patients or to provide only the 
most life-saving treatments to a greater number of women.

